# Linea Supply — Cursor agent

You are working in a **FastAPI + React (Vite)** monorepo (SQLite). Follow the repo contract and shell commands below.

## Workflow with the user (mandatory)

1. **Plan first** — At the start of each user request (or when direction changes), state a short **numbered plan**: what you will read or inspect, what you will change, how you will verify (tests, `just check` / `just lint`, manual check). On follow-up turns in the same task, give a one-line plan update if the approach shifted; if unchanged, proceed and say so briefly.
2. **Clarify the ideal outcome** — Before substantial implementation (multi-file work, new behavior, UX, API shape, or non-obvious trade-offs), ask **concrete questions** until “done” is clear: scope boundaries, acceptance criteria, preferred UX/copy, compatibility, deadlines, or “what would perfect look like?” Do not guess silently when those matter. If the request is already fully specified, state your **interpretation in one short paragraph** and execute. For trivial one-step fixes (typo, obvious single-line bug with one fix), a minimal plan plus stated assumptions is enough without a long Q&A.

## Read first (do not skip)

1. **`AGENTS.md`** (repo root) — short table of links + knowledge base rules.
2. **`vault/agent/index.md`** — specs, engineering workflow, vault map (Russian index; paths are stable).
3. For code you touch: **`backend/AGENTS.md`** or **`frontend/AGENTS.md`**.

## Commands (run from repository root)

Use **`just`** — see **`justfile`** or `just --list`.

| Goal | Command |
|------|---------|
| Format backend + frontend | `just format` |
| Lint / typecheck backend | `just check` |
| Lint frontend | `just lint` |
| Production build (frontend) | `just build` |
| Full local CI (mirror pipeline) | `just ci` |
| Full verification, all steps even if one fails (report) | `just ci-all-steps` — see `scripts/ci-all-steps.sh` |
| Background dev servers + logs | `just dev-headless` → `just logs` → **`just stop`** when done |
| Seed DB | `just seed` |

Prefer these over ad-hoc one-liners unless you need a single targeted command.

## Ports and URLs

- Frontend: `http://localhost:3001`
- Backend OpenAPI: `http://localhost:8001/docs`

